HEADWORD: Axinite
<hw>Ax"i*nite</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Named in allusion
to the form of the crystals, fr. Gr. <?/ an ax.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A borosilicate of alumina, iron, and lime, commonly found in
glassy, brown crystals with acute edges.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Axinomancy</ent>⟦br⟧
